ABC Corp. seems to be more mechanical. Formalization, centralization, and specialization define mechanistic organizations. They have a clear hierarchy, positions, and command structure. ABC Corp. has a CEO to whom everyone reports, well-documented processes and job descriptions, and limited decision-making power for low-level staff. Organic organizations are more flexible, decentralized, and employee-autonomous. With a flat structure and fewer restrictive roles and duties, they are more flexible. In conclusion, ABC Corp. has a more mechanical structure due to its high degree of formalization, centralization, and specialized roles and duties, which is appropriate for a stable environment with moderate changes and stable product categories. 